{{Thermoreg}}'''Bradyaerobic''' is a term used in [[biology]] that describes an [[animal]] that has low levels of [[Blood|oxygen consumption]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = Terramegathermy: Table 2, Refs, Definitions|url = http://dml.cmnh.org/2001Apr/msg00379.html|website = dml.cmnh.org|accessdate = 2015-12-07}}</ref>  

By necessity a bradyaerobic animal can engage in short low or high low-level aerobic activities, followed by brief anaerobically powered bursts of energy.  Bradyaerobes can be sprinters, but not long distance animals.<ref>{{Cite book|title = Dinosaurs of the Air: The Evolution and Loss of Flight in Dinosaurs and Birds|url = https://books.google.com/books?id=OUwXzD3iihAC|publisher = JHU Press|date = 2002-04-01|isbn = 9780801867637|first = Gregory S.|last = Paul}}</ref>

