{{Infobox person | name = Columba McVeigh | birth_name = | birth_date = 1958 | birth_place = [[Donaghmore, County Tyrone|Donaghmore]], [[County Tyrone]], [[Northern Ireland]] | disappeared_date = 1 November 1975 (aged 17) | disappeared_place = | disappeared_status = {{Missing for|1975|11|1}} | monuments = | nationality = [[Irish people|Irish]] }}
'''Columba McVeigh''' (1958 – 1 November 1975) was a youth from [[Northern Ireland]] who was abducted and murdered by the [[Provisional Irish Republican Army]] (IRA). He was listed as one of the "Disappeared" by the [[Independent Commission for the Location of Victims' Remains]].
==Disappearance== A seventeen-year-old from [[Donaghmore, County Tyrone|Donaghmore]], [[County Tyrone]], McVeigh disappeared in November 1975. The IRA allege he had confessed to being a [[British Army]] [[secret agent|intelligence agent]] who had received orders to infiltrate the IRA's ranks,<ref name=":1">Rosie Cowan, [https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2002/sep/30/northernireland.northernireland1 "Adams 'at heart' of IRA's most shameful killing campaign"], ''The Guardian'', 30 September 2002.</ref> however it has never indicated what specific act prompted McVeigh's murder.<ref name=":0"/> A number of unsuccessful searches have been carried out for the location of his body since 1999, notably in 2003, 2011, and 2012.<ref name=":0">[http://www.thejournal.ie/search-bog-monaghan-columba-mcveigh-599082-Sep2012/ Search for teenage IRA victim resumes at Co Monaghan bog], ''The Journal'', Sep 18, 2012</ref> In September 2018 forensic archaeologists started searching Braggan Bog, near [[Emyvale]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2018/sep/17/columba-mcveigh-fresh-search-for-remains-ira-victim|title=Columba McVeigh: fresh search for remains of IRA victim|publisher=[[The Guardian]]|last=Carroll|first=Rory|date=17 September 2018|accessdate=18 September 2018}}</ref>
