{{Infobox military person | name = Francisco de Becerra | image = | caption = | birth_date = 1510s | death_date = 16th century | placeofburial_label = | placeofburial = | birth_place = [[Medellín, Spain|Medellín]], [[Extremadura]], [[Spain]] | death_place = [[Colonial Brazil|Brazil]] | placeofburial_coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LONG|display=inline,title}} --> | nickname = | birth_name = | allegiance = [[File:Flag of New Spain.svg|border|20px]] [[Spain]] | branch = | serviceyears = | rank = [[Captain (armed forces)|Captain]] | servicenumber = | unit = | commands = | battles = | battles_label = | awards = | relations = | laterwork = }}
'''Francisco de Becerra''' (1510s, [[Medellín, Spain|Medellín]], [[Extremadura]], [[Spanish Empire|Spain]] - ?, [[Colonial Brazil|Brazil]]) was a Spanish nobleman, served as Captain in the [[Spanish Army]], during the conquest of the [[New World]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Hernandarias: primer gran estanciero criollo del Río de la Plata |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=O7hoAAAAMAAJ&q=francisco+becerra+mencia+calderon&dq=francisco+becerra+mencia+calderon&hl=es-419&sa=X&ei=uJNyVOOmD-nIsQShnYC4Aw&ved=0CD4Q6AEwBg |year= |publisher=Carlos M. Aranguren}}</ref>
== Biography == Born in [[Extremadura]] in the 1510s, Becerra was commander of the [[brigantine]] who brought to [[Mencía Calderón]] in 1550.<ref>{{cite book|title=Mujeres de la Conquista |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=I45Mqb4I2EoC&pg=PT87&dq=francisco+becerra+mencia+calderon&hl=es-419&sa=X&ei=0aZyVNaLPPf_sASbuIKQBA&ved=0CBsQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=francisco%20becerra%20mencia%20calderon&f=false |year= |publisher=Lucía Gálvez}}</ref> On that trip Becerra was accompanied by his wife Isabel, daughter of [[Álvaro Contreras y Carvajal]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Hombres y mujeres de Ámerica: diccionario biográfico-genealógico de nuestros progenitores, siglos XVI-XIX |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=TUMrAQAAIAAJ&q=francisco+becerra+%C3%81lvaro+de+Contreras+y+Carvajal&dq=francisco+becerra+%C3%81lvaro+de+Contreras+y+Carvajal&hl=es-419&sa=X&ei=YJZyVJeTFOmCsQSF1IHAAQ&ved=0CBsQ6AEwAA |year= |publisher=Carlos B. Vega}}</ref> He lost his life on the same trip, due to a shipwreck in Mbiazá, Brazil. His wife and children managed to save their lives.<ref>{{cite book|title=Paraguay: destino y esperanza |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Hdl8AAAAMAAJ&q=francisco+becerra+bergantin&dq=francisco+becerra+bergantin&hl=es-419&sa=X&ei=bqByVIb_MKbHsQS2v4D4CA&ved=0CEYQ6AEwCA |year= |publisher=Pastor Urbieta Rojas}}</ref>
